    "recap_headline": "University of Richmond Athletics",
    "recap_text": "BRONX, NY \u2013\nThe Richmond baseball team scored first and scored last to defeat the Fordham Rams, 4-3, Saturday afternoon at Houlihan Family Park in Atlantic 10 Conference action.\nRichmond, 12-11 on the year and 1-4 in league play, and Fordham, 10-11 on the season and 3-1 in conference action, return to Houlihan Park Sunday for the rubber match of the series. First pitch is set for 12 p.m. and the game will be streamed on ESPN+.\nBoth starting pitchers were dueling to start the game, but Richmond struck first with an RBI base hit by\nChris Schaller\nto score\nSean Scanlon\nfrom second.\nRichmond starter\nJoey Giordano\nhad a no-hitter through three and two-thirds of an inning but stranded the runners. Fordham got on the board in the fifth inning, tagging Giordano with two unearned runs on two hits and a UR miscue to take a 2-1 lead. The Rams extended their lead to 3-1 in the seventh, scoring a run on a bunt single in front of the mound.\nRichmond roared back in the top of the eighth. With one out, Kennedy singled through the middle then moved up to second on a wild pitch.\nRJ Johnson Jr.\nhit his third home run of the season to right field to tie the game at 3-3.\nDylan Winebrenner\nbrought in the go-ahead run with a base hit to left field, pushing in\nReid Downs\nfrom second. Downs took over on the base paths for pinch-hitter\nRJ Rickabaugh\nafter he drew a walk.\nBijan Anvar\ntook over for Giordano with two outs in the eighth. Anvar retired all four batters he faced to collect his first save of the season. Giordano moves to 5-0 on the season with the win.",
